  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "During the removal of a submucosal fibroid by hysteroscopy, a deficit of 2000 mL is estimated in a patient. What is the immediate complication of this?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Acute tubular necrosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "DIC"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Pulmonary edema"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Thromboembolism"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: C) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10e2dee19e1692777196673db90c23\">Pulmonary</span> edema</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The immediate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> of a fluid deficit (the amount of fluid absorbed by the body) of 2000mL during <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f512f18b011692777189e09aa21e98\">hysteroscopy</span> is<strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10e2dee19e1692777196673db90c23\">pulmonary</span> oedema. </strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Hysteroscopy and distension fluid: </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Hysteroscopy is both a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8dfaeedbf91692777200561b2b1d2f\">therapeutic</span> procedure</li>\n\t<li>Fluid distension is done to improve <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"33ba8d60fb16927772029d1067e602\">visualization</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> cavity</li>\n\t<li>For <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"791dbee3ff1692777192bf25e5fbd1\">monopolar</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> instruments: Electrolyte-free, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6c1412e72916927771893d06180642\">hypotonic</span> solutions are used</li>\n\t<li>For <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"df4ae006fe1692777183604169e9b2\">bipolar</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> instruments: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"28f696d61216927771904dbe51b33b\">Isotonic</span> distension fluids can be used</li>\n\t<li>A fluid deficit is a difference in the amount of distension fluid inserted and removed, which makes up the amount absorbed by the body.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p>A <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> associated with hysteroscopic procedures is <strong>excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fcb9396d1169277718069dd7fa788\">absorption</span> of media.</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Distension media</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Feature </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Complications </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Carbon dioxide</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Highly <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"845fedd06d16927771989597afa034\">soluble</span> in blood so poses less risk</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>The flow rate must be below 100ml/min</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Insufflation pressure must be < 100mmHg</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>CO<sub>2 </sub>emboli (rare)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Intraoperative morbidity</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Death</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Dextran 70</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hyperosmolar medium</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Volume used should be < 300ml</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Allergic reaction (rare)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Coagulopathy (rare)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vascular overload</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Heart failure</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2313fc54841692777202a008c72950\">viscosity</span> fluids</p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>1.5% glycine</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>3% sorbitol</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>5% mannitol</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hypotonic</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Electrolyte free</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Absorption leads to major volume and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e0552462e16927771871413861fb7\">electrolyte</span> disturbances</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pulmonary oedema</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hyponatremia</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Heart failure</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Cerebral edema</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Death</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Cardiac and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3323d4b271692777200122ea879e5\">toxicity</span> (from glycine)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Other complications of hysteroscopy:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Uterine perforation</li>\n\t<li>Hemorrhage</li>\n\t<li>Gas embolism</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Acute <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"98d387b7bd1692777201278b27be72\">tubular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5e84a7987c16927771931012aced83\">necrosis</span> (ATN)</strong> <strong>(Option A) </strong>is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">kidney</span> disorder involving damage to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> tubules, usually due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0f670d10711692777190af4b12fac9\">ischemia</span> (lack of blood supply) or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0834e545c9169277719383768d0ff2\">nephrotoxic</span> agents. While severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"da07fd59a11692777185e23c69af5e\">dehydration</span> can lead to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">kidney</span> injury, ATN is not the immediate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> resulting from a fluid deficit during a hysteroscopic procedure.</p>\n\n<p><strong>DIC (Option B) </strong>is a serious condition characterized by widespread <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ba6b77f29316927771807350f86ce2\">activation</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"58c17961c71692777184ab55a9c4df\">clotting</span> cascade, leading to the formation of microclots throughout the bloodstream. This excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"58c17961c71692777184ab55a9c4df\">clotting</span> consumes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"58c17961c71692777184ab55a9c4df\">clotting</span> factors and platelets, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> tendencies elsewhere in the body. It occurs with significant fluid loss.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Thromboembolism</strong> <strong>(Option D) </strong>refers to the formation of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"40d68b98721692777183c42090e023\">blood clot</span> that dislodges and travels through the bloodstream, potentially causing blockages in vital organs. While <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"58c17961c71692777184ab55a9c4df\">clotting</span> issues can arise from factors related to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"da07fd59a11692777185e23c69af5e\">dehydration</span> and surgery, immediate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"237b2a1dfa1692777200a074fd1072\">thromboembolism</span> is not a direct <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> of a fluid deficit during a hysteroscopic procedure.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
