    {
      "text": "For which of the following diagnoses in the given OT list would hysteroscopy be the preferred procedure?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Tubal ligation"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Asherman syndrome"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Cervical polyp"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Subserosal fibroid"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) Asherman syndrome</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Asherman syndrome</strong> is the spectrum of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e9dcc3d4241692777198c7030bf313\">scarring</span> due to firm adhesions, dense bands or complete <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e5922b669a169277719487f8bbabd3\">obliteration</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> cavity, which must be evaluated by hysteroscopy.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Hysteroscopy</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Indications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Diagnostic:</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>AUB</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Infertility <strong>(Asherman syndrome) </strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Recurrent miscarriage<strong> (Asherman syndrome)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Congenital <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">Uterine</span> Anomalies</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Therapeutic:</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Lost or displaced IUD</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Uterine septum</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Polyps</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Leiomyomas: It is preferred for fibroids below 5cm</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Endometrial ablation</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hysteroscopic sterilization</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Intrauterine adhesions</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Proximal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a970a38e85169277720171bea632e7\">tubal</span> obstruction</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Procedure</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Position: Modified <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51b29c48291692777186b488ac8cd9\">dorsal</span> lithotomy</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Cervical exposure</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Anesthesia: Based on the patient’s requirement</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Cervical dilation</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Uterine distention</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Visualization and imaging</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Intrauterine cutting and hemostasis</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Other instrumentation: Based on the patient's condition.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Contraindications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Active <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"25c6ce766c1692777184ab9a40305c\">cervical</span> infections</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Large <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ddba4206eb169277718335596e86da\">cavity</span> ( > 10 cm in length)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Confirmed <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"25c6ce766c1692777184ab9a40305c\">cervical</span> or endometrial cancer</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pregnancy.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Tubal ligation</strong> <strong>(Option A)</strong>, also known as female sterilization, is a procedure performed to block or seal the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efc83dab2c1692777202b5d1d06c4f\">fallopian</span> tubes, thereby preventing the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2a8e411e2116927772022dd4b365bc\">fertilization</span> of eggs by sperm. This procedure does not involve the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> cavity, so <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f512f18b011692777189e09aa21e98\">hysteroscopy</span> would not be necessary for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a970a38e85169277720171bea632e7\">tubal</span> ligation.</p>\n\n<p>A <strong>cervical polyp</strong> <strong>(Option C)</strong> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1bbae82f1f16927771824f797639fa\">benign</span> growth that arises from the inner lining of the cervix. It does not involve the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ddba4206eb169277718335596e86da\">cavity</span> but rather protrudes into the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"25c6ce766c1692777184ab9a40305c\">cervical</span> canal. Therefore, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f512f18b011692777189e09aa21e98\">hysteroscopy</span> is not typically required for the diagnosis or removal of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"25c6ce766c1692777184ab9a40305c\">cervical</span> polyp.</p>\n\n<p>A <strong>subserosal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc32fa81216927772024a5075bf66\">fibroid</span> </strong> <strong>(Option D)</strong> is a type of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc32fa81216927772024a5075bf66\">fibroid</span> that grows on the outer surface of the uterus. It does not protrude into the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> cavity, so <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f512f18b011692777189e09aa21e98\">hysteroscopy</span> is not necessary for its diagnosis or treatment.</p>",
