    {
      "text": "A 46-year-old woman presents with complaints of irregular menstrual cycles and heavy vaginal bleeding for several months. Transvaginal ultrasound reveals an endometrial thickness of 16 mm. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Hysterectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Start combined oral contraceptive pills"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Observe and reassess after a few months"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Perform an endometrial biopsy"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Answer: D. Perform an endometrial biopsy</strong></p>\n\n<h3><strong>Explanation: </strong></h3>\n\n<p>In a perimenopausal woman (>45 years) with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"458e050fdc16927771809854c9fd53\">abnormal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> (AUB), the major concern is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"32312bbe131692777187438292b62d\">endometrial hyperplasia</span> or carcinoma.</p>\n\n<p>Endometrial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"754ab07a2e1692777183ed178c883d\">biopsy</span> is the first-line <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> step to rule out malignancy, especially when:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Endometrial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"facd67f6341692777200653d383689\">thickness</span> >4 mm in postmenopausal</li>\n\t<li>Persistent AUB in perimenopausal</li>\n\t<li>Risk factors: obesity, unopposed estrogen, diabetes, family history of endometrial cancer</li>\n\t<li>Here, the woman is 46 years old (perimenopausal) with heavy <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> and endometrial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"facd67f6341692777200653d383689\">thickness</span> of 16 mm → <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"754ab07a2e1692777183ed178c883d\">biopsy</span> is warranted before starting any treatment.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:614px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Situation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Endometrial Thickness</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Prepubertal</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>< 5 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Reproductive age – Menstrual phase (Day 1–4)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>1–4 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Early <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c1f9aa614f169277719662c5fe3231\">proliferative phase</span> (Day 5–9)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>4–8 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Late proliferative / Pre-ovulatory (Day 10–14)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>6–10 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Secretory phase (Day 15–28)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>7–14 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Postmenopausal (on HRT)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>≤ 8 mm</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Postmenopausal (no HRT)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>≤ 4 mm (≥ 5 mm suspicious for malignancy)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Hysterectomy (Option A)</strong>: Definitive treatment but not the first step without a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1e9c8202241692777189dbac6cc062\">histological</span> diagnosis. Only done if <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0c7efd2b8716927771914c8cb19e54\">malignancy</span> or severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"06123ff61a1692777182e19b790ebc\">atypical</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4c5d5ef6c31692777189820d4b320d\">hyperplasia</span> is confirmed and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2238ef34bc16927772024c3becf614\">fertility</span> is not desired.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Start <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fcb0512bcc16927771851fe5a081f6\">combined oral contraceptive</span> pills (Option B): </strong>May control <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1bbae82f1f16927771824f797639fa\">benign</span> cases but starting without ruling out <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0c7efd2b8716927771914c8cb19e54\">malignancy</span> is unsafe. Hormones can mask symptoms and delay diagnosis.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Observe and reassess after a few months (Option C): </strong>Delays diagnosis of possible cancer. In high-risk age group with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"458e050fdc16927771809854c9fd53\">abnormal</span> bleeding, observation is not acceptable.<br />\n </p>",
